race.comment: SOO KISS ME (5) finished out of the money but was not too far away when resuming last start at Jerilderie. Can improve sharply. KING CZAR (1) was very disappointing fresh but is capable of a much stronger showing with that run out of the way. Is drawn to advantage on the inside and is worth following up. WARLIST (7) is yet to fire a shot fresh but does boast peak figures that measure right up. Readied with a solid Geelong jump-out and gets in well with the claim. Not without his chance. KILMISTER (6) got home strongly last start to finish a close third over this trip at Murtoa. Among the better chances. FLYING D'AMORE (9) is experiencing a long win drought but is knocking on the door and should find this easier.
